594
00:33:06,940 --> 00:33:08,260
Okay. What's her name?

595
00:33:33,660 --> 00:33:34,220
Come on.

596
00:33:34,860 --> 00:33:35,660
Take it slow.

597
00:33:36,380 --> 00:33:36,980
Careful.

598
00:33:38,260 --> 00:33:39,020
Slow down.

599
00:33:39,100 --> 00:33:39,820
Okay.

600
00:33:51,700 --> 00:33:52,300
Okay.

601
00:33:52,780 --> 00:33:53,380
Okay.

602
00:34:03,340 --> 00:34:03,900
Enough.

603
00:34:04,020 --> 00:34:05,100
We'll stop here today.

604
00:34:05,340 --> 00:34:05,940
Okay?

605
00:34:06,140 --> 00:34:06,900
I'm fine.

606
00:34:07,580 --> 00:34:08,380
Let's go.

607
00:34:09,180 --> 00:34:10,100
We try again.

608
00:34:10,460 --> 00:34:10,900
Okay.

609
00:34:13,700 --> 00:34:14,300
I'm fine.

610
00:34:15,900 --> 00:34:16,740
Be careful.

611
00:34:27,580 --> 00:34:28,620
He couldn't go on.

612
00:34:28,660 --> 00:34:29,780
Just stop here.

613
00:34:30,740 --> 00:34:32,260
Okay, we can take it slow.

614
00:34:35,140 --> 00:34:35,660
Here.

615
00:34:36,220 --> 00:34:36,940
Careful.

616
00:34:45,620 --> 00:34:47,100
- No need to hurry, okay?
- Thank you.

617
00:34:51,460 --> 00:34:51,900
Here.

618
00:35:04,340 --> 00:35:05,100
Mr. Fu.

619
00:35:05,260 --> 00:35:06,580
Well done.

620
00:35:06,740 --> 00:35:07,780
Here's your reward.

621
00:35:13,700 --> 00:35:14,380
Thank you.

622
00:35:16,140 --> 00:35:18,260
The beginning is always the hardest.

623
00:35:18,700 --> 00:35:20,860
Imagine yourself
as a toddler learning to walk.

624
00:35:21,180 --> 00:35:22,820
Let me tell you a secret.

625
00:35:24,340 --> 00:35:25,940
I only learned to walk when I was two.

626
00:35:26,660 --> 00:35:28,180
What? Two?

627
00:35:28,700 --> 00:35:29,620
That's slow.

628
00:35:32,140 --> 00:35:33,540
Granny thought

629
00:35:33,660 --> 00:35:35,580
something was wrong with my body.

630
00:35:35,700 --> 00:35:36,900
However,

631
00:35:37,500 --> 00:35:39,300
nothing's wrong with my body,

632
00:35:40,860 --> 00:35:41,740
I'm just slow.

633
00:35:42,740 --> 00:35:43,980
Do you mean up here?

634
00:35:45,060 --> 00:35:45,700
Zhu Jiu, you're not slow.

635
00:35:45,780 --> 00:35:46,700
You're a genius.

636
00:35:49,020 --> 00:35:50,580
Scratch that.

637
00:35:50,700 --> 00:35:53,420
I had a hard time
back in my school days.

638
00:35:53,740 --> 00:35:55,420
When I was little, my first goal

639
00:35:55,500 --> 00:35:57,140
is my parents' alma mater,

640
00:35:57,420 --> 00:35:59,300
Heidelberg University School
of Medicine.

641
00:36:00,020 --> 00:36:00,780
You're ambitious.

642
00:36:01,740 --> 00:36:02,380
Therefore,

643
00:36:02,460 --> 00:36:05,420
I must get admitted
to the best university in China

644
00:36:05,540 --> 00:36:07,220
to earn that eligibility
to apply for it.

645
00:36:07,580 --> 00:36:09,060
I spent most of my high school days

646
00:36:09,140 --> 00:36:11,180
on studying.

647
00:36:11,300 --> 00:36:12,780
I had no time
for extracurricular activities.

648
00:36:13,300 --> 00:36:14,300
Wasn't it boring?

649
00:36:15,660 --> 00:36:16,540
No, it's pretty good.

650
00:36:17,300 --> 00:36:19,180
Stop thinking nonsense.

651
00:36:19,860 --> 00:36:20,780
- Let go.
- No.

652
00:36:21,180 --> 00:36:21,860
Let go.

653
00:36:22,140 --> 00:36:22,660
Okay.

654
00:36:25,420 --> 00:36:26,030
I had bad luck

655
00:36:26,030 --> 00:36:27,980
when I was in my senior year
in high school.

656
00:36:28,100 --> 00:36:30,220
I got a fever just before the exam.

657
00:36:30,660 --> 00:36:32,500
So, I had to have an intravenous drip.

658
00:36:32,740 --> 00:36:34,980
But it made me feel drowsy.

659
00:36:35,140 --> 00:36:37,020
So I drank a lot of coffee.

660
00:36:37,340 --> 00:36:38,780
Granny felt sorry for me.

661
00:36:38,940 --> 00:36:40,060
She said

662
00:36:40,220 --> 00:36:41,900
that I was still young,

663
00:36:42,140 --> 00:36:43,340
I could repeat the grade

664
00:36:43,500 --> 00:36:44,860
if I failed.

665
00:36:46,820 --> 00:36:48,660
But Leo told me

666
00:36:48,900 --> 00:36:53,100
you skipped a grade
when you were in university.

667
00:36:53,500 --> 00:36:55,020
It turns out you worked so hard.

668
00:36:56,540 --> 00:36:57,300
In this world,

669
00:36:57,380 --> 00:36:59,500
not many are born geniuses.

670
00:36:59,780 --> 00:37:02,140
The majority of us have to strive hard

671
00:37:02,220 --> 00:37:03,540
to achieve the results.

672
00:37:04,180 --> 00:37:05,220
You reap

673
00:37:05,420 --> 00:37:06,260
what you sow.

674
00:37:06,980 --> 00:37:07,540
Do you agree?

675
00:37:08,780 --> 00:37:09,780
That's true.

676
00:37:13,900 --> 00:37:14,580
Yunshen.

677
00:37:15,420 --> 00:37:16,180
I'm sorry.

678
00:37:16,780 --> 00:37:17,980
You're trying so hard.

679
00:37:18,540 --> 00:37:20,180
But I can't help you much.

680
00:37:21,580 --> 00:37:23,180
It's not hard at all.

681
00:37:23,660 --> 00:37:24,460
Liar.

682
00:37:24,980 --> 00:37:25,620
I mean it.

683
00:37:27,100 --> 00:37:28,500
As long as you're with me,

684
00:37:30,060 --> 00:37:31,460
nothing is hard for me.

685
00:37:39,620 --> 00:37:40,580
Mr. Fu.

686
00:37:41,380 --> 00:37:43,060
You are honey-tongued.

687
00:37:43,580 --> 00:37:45,420
You must have dated many girls, right?

688
00:37:48,660 --> 00:37:50,900
Dr. Zhu, you're sharp-eyed.

689
00:37:51,060 --> 00:37:52,780
Did you get tricked a lot back then?

690
00:37:53,420 --> 00:37:54,740
Impossible.

691
00:37:55,220 --> 00:37:56,980
No one has the guts to deceive me.

692
00:37:57,180 --> 00:37:58,060
Neither do you.

693
00:37:59,340 --> 00:38:00,060
Ouch.

694
00:38:13,580 --> 00:38:14,460
It's not that I daren't,

695
00:38:17,700 --> 00:38:18,580
it's that I don't want to.

696
00:38:20,700 --> 00:38:21,900
And I won't do that.

697
00:38:23,220 --> 00:38:23,740
Zhu Jiu.

698
00:38:26,620 --> 00:38:27,860
In this world,

699
00:38:29,540 --> 00:38:30,700
you're the unique presence

700
00:38:32,660 --> 00:38:34,300
for me.

701
00:38:36,570 --> 00:38:37,620
You're also the best answer

702
00:38:39,580 --> 00:38:40,660
in my heart.

703
00:39:08,620 --> 00:39:10,420
The operation was a success.

704
00:39:10,620 --> 00:39:13,380
Subsequent test results have been good.

705
00:39:14,100 --> 00:39:16,180
But why can't we see the improvement?

706
00:39:17,300 --> 00:39:20,540
It's true that Mr. Fu's progress

707
00:39:20,740 --> 00:39:22,940
is slower than we expected.

708
00:39:23,300 --> 00:39:26,340
If we don't see a meaningful recovery
in three months,

709
00:39:26,780 --> 00:39:28,860
clinically or physiologically,

710
00:39:29,020 --> 00:39:31,860
we'll have to perform
an exploratory surgery.

711
00:39:37,740 --> 00:39:42,940
In the patient's recovery,
in addition to the physiological aspect,

712
00:39:43,060 --> 00:39:44,980
there's also psychological work.

713
00:39:45,140 --> 00:39:47,100
It requires

714
00:39:47,300 --> 00:39:49,980
passion and a positive attitude

715
00:39:50,100 --> 00:39:51,780
to achieve good results.

716
00:39:52,580 --> 00:39:53,180
But...

717
00:39:53,740 --> 00:39:56,700
This also goes for his family members.

718
00:39:57,340 --> 00:39:58,220
Thank you.

719
00:40:00,060 --> 00:40:01,100
Have a nice day.

